text: Kanak or similar may mean: * Kanak Peak, a mountain in Antarctica * Kanak people, an Oceanic people * Orang Kanaq, a Proto-Malay Orang Asli group of people also known as Kanaq or Kanak people * Kanake or Kanaker, a derogatory word used in German-speaking countries * Kanak Chanpa Chakma (born 1963), Bangladeshi artist * Katharine Kanak (born ), American atmospheric scientist ==See also== * Baduy people, a branch of the Sundanese people also known as Kanekes people * Canuck /kəˈnʌk/, a slang term for a Canadian * Kanaka (Pacific Island worker)
title: Kanak (disambiguation)
